  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When I got the key name or `validatorselectionmode` enum value wrong in the transitions config, my config was either ignored or I got incorrect behaviour at runtime.\n\nAn improvement would be to throw an error whenever an invalid key or enum value is attempted.\n\nA further improvement would be to make a useful suggestion for the user, e.g. user types 'validatormode', respond with \"Did you mean validatorselectionmode?\"\nOr at least list enumerate the possible keys/values.",
